<article class="docs-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Documentation</p>
    <h1>Server-rendered partials that stay useful with HTMX</h1>
    <p class="lead">go-partial is a small rendering layer for Go applications that want reusable template regions, targeted updates, out-of-band swaps, and predictable server-side behavior.</p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="primary-action" href="/docs/installation" hx-get="/docs/installation" hx-target="#content" hx-push-url="true">Get started</a>
        <a class="secondary-action" href="/docs/api" hx-get="/docs/api" hx-target="#content" hx-push-url="true">Read the API</a>
    </div>

